amarantin installation
======================

Overview
--------
amarantin is a C++17 / ROOT project for building and processing ROOT-based
sample, dataset, and event-list containers.

The supported installation path documented here is the CMake build. Older
build artifacts may still exist in the tree, but they are not the primary
path described below.

Repository layout
-----------------
io/         Core I/O library
ana/        Analysis-side helpers and event-list construction
syst/       Systematics cache construction
plot/       Plotting library
app/        Command-line tools
tools/      Helper scripts
cmake/      CMake package config template
Dockerfile  Portable development container

What gets built
---------------
Libraries
  * IO
  * Ana
  * Syst
  * Plot
  * Fit

Executables
  * mk_sample
  * mk_dataset
  * mk_eventlist
  * mk_dist
  * mk_fit
  * mk_cov

Prerequisites
-------------
Required
  * CMake 3.16 or newer
  * C++17 compiler
  * ROOT
  * SQLite3 development files

Optional
  * nlohmann_json headers or package

ROOT may be provided either as a CMake package via `ROOT_DIR` or via
`root-config` on `PATH`.

Quick start
-----------
Out-of-source builds are required.

  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build --parallel

Additional named build trees
----------------------------
If you need more than one local build, keep them under the hidden `.build/`
parent instead of creating more root-level `build-*` or `cmake-build-*`
directories:

  tools/configure-build host
  cmake --build .build/host --parallel

Build only selected targets
---------------------------
  cmake --build build --target IO
  cmake --build build --target Ana
  cmake --build build --target Syst
  cmake --build build --target Plot
  cmake --build build --target Fit
  cmake --build build --target mk_sample
  cmake --build build --target mk_dataset
  cmake --build build --target mk_eventlist
  cmake --build build --target mk_dist
  cmake --build build --target mk_fit
  cmake --build build --target mk_cov

Install
-------
Install into the configured prefix:

  cmake --install build

Install into a local prefix:

  cmake -S . -B build \
    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
    -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="$PWD/install"
  cmake --build build --parallel
  cmake --install build

GPVM / Fermilab workflow
------------------------
On supported Fermilab systems, the repository provides helper scripts for the
expected container and product setup:

  source ./.container.sh
  source ./.setup.sh
  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build --parallel

Docker workflow
---------------
Build the portable development image from the repository root:

  docker build -t amarantin-dev .

Open a shell in the container:

  docker run --rm -it -v "$PWD":/work -w /work amarantin-dev bash

Then configure and build inside the container:

  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build --parallel

Configuration notes
-------------------
ROOT discovery
  Preferred:
    cmake -S . -B build -DROOT_DIR=/path/to/dir/containing/ROOTConfig.cmake

  Fallback:
    Put root-config on PATH before running CMake.

Optional JSON headers
  If nlohmann_json is needed but no CMake package is available:

    cmake -S . -B build -DNLOHMANN_JSON_INC=/path/to/include

Applications
  The command-line tools are built by default. To build the libraries without
  the applications:

    cmake -S . -B build -DAMARANTIN_BUILD_APP=OFF

Runtime note for systematics cache builds
-----------------------------------------
`mk_dist` accepts `--genie-knobs` to persist the optional paired
`weightsGenieUp` / `weightsGenieDn` source-shift lane when those branches are
present on the selected-event tree. The logical flux family prefers
`weightsPPFX` and falls back to `weightsFlux`.

Runtime note for SBNFit export
------------------------------
`mk_cov` now also supports `--manifest` to export a stacked
multi-process covariance matrix. In that mode it correlates detector and
`genie_knobs` lanes only by shared source labels, and correlates multisim
families only when retained universes survive with matching family branch name
and universe count across all contributing rows.

Installed files
---------------
Typical installed outputs are:

  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_sample
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_dataset
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_eventlist
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_dist
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_fit
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR}/mk_cov
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/libIO.<shared-library>
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/libAna.<shared-library>
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/libSyst.<shared-library>
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/libPlot.<shared-library>
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/libFit.<shared-library>
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/ShardIO.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/DistributionIO.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/EventListIO.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/DatasetIO.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/SampleIO.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}/amarantin/SignalStrengthFit.hh
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/cmake/amarantin/amarantinConfig.cmake
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/cmake/amarantin/amarantinConfigVersion.cmake
  ${prefix}/${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}/cmake/amarantin/amarantinTargets.cmake

Downstream CMake use
--------------------
  find_package(amarantin CONFIG REQUIRED)

  target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE amarantin::IO)
  # or
  target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE amarantin::Ana)
  # or
  target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE amarantin::Syst)
  # or
  target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE amarantin::Plot)
  # or
  target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE amarantin::Fit)

Verification
------------
After a successful build, the build tree should contain:

  build/bin/mk_sample
  build/bin/mk_dataset
  build/bin/mk_eventlist
  build/bin/mk_dist
  build/bin/mk_fit
  build/bin/mk_cov
  build/lib/

A simple smoke test is:

  build/bin/mk_sample --help

A focused stacked-export smoke, once the ROOT build is available, is:

  tools/systematics-sbnfit-export-smoke.sh

Runtime note for mk_sample
--------------------------
mk_sample accepts an optional SQLite run database path via `--run-db PATH`.
Its native logical-sample form is:

  mk_sample --sample NAME --manifest SAMPLE.manifest output.root [origin] [variation] [beam] [polarity]

Manifest rows are:

  shard sample-list-path

The older positional `output.root input.list ...` form remains available as a
transitional bridge. If you still need a file containing many list paths, pass
it as `@path`.

If `--run-db` is not provided, it checks `AMARANTIN_RUN_DB`. If that is
unset, it falls back to:

  /exp/uboone/data/uboonebeam/beamdb/run.db
